SIMPLE: preferment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preferment
<hw>Pre*fer"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of choosing, or the state of being chosen; preference.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Natural <qex>preferment</qex> of the one . . . before the
other.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of preferring, or advancing in dignity or
office; the state of being advanced; promotion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Neither royal blandishments nor promises of valuable
<qex>preferment</qex> had been spared.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A position or office of honor or profit; <as>as, the
<ex>preferments</ex> of the church</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preferrer</ent>⟦br⟧
